  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Magnetic endoscope imaging (MEI) is already used in colonoscopy in order facilitate scope
      navigation. In this study the use of MEI will be evaluated for small bowel enteroscopy in
      which scope navigation is particularly important. The MEI will be compared with x-ray which
      is still the current gold standard for scope navigation in small bowel enteroscopy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
